articles.description: RAFAH, Gaza Strip (AP) — Israeli forces rescued two hostages early Monday, storming a heavily guarded apartment in the Gaza Strip and extracting the captives under fire in a dramatic raid that was a small but symbolically significant success for Israel.
articles.title: Israeli forces rescue 2 hostages in dramatic Gaza raid that killed at least 67 Palestinians

articles.author: JULIA FRANKEL
articles.description: JERUSALEM (AP) — It was a warm handshake between the unlikeliest of statesmen, conducted under the beaming gaze of President Jimmy Carter. Sunlight streamed through the trees at Camp David, Maryland, as Egyptian President Anwar Sadat and Israeli Prime Minister Menachem Begin solidified a landmark agreement that has allowed over 40 years of peace between Israel and Egypt.
articles.title: Egypt is threatening to void its decades-old peace treaty with Israel. What does that mean?

articles.author: ROB MAADDI
articles.description: LAS VEGAS (AP) — Patrick Mahomes, Travis Kelce and Andy Reid have made the Kansas City Chiefs a dynasty.They’re already thinking three-peat.First, they had to become the first back-to-back Super Bowl champions in 19 years.
articles.title: Patrick Mahomes rallies the Chiefs to second straight Super Bowl title, 25-22 over 49ers in overtime

articles.author: JUAN A. LOZANO
articles.description: HOUSTON (AP) — A woman’s motive for opening fire in celebrity pastor Joel Osteen’s megachurch remained unclear Monday, a day after the shooting sent worshippers rushing for safety in between busy services.
articles.title: What to know about a shooting at Joel Osteen's megachurch in Texas during Sunday services

articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Nikki Haley is challenging Donald Trump to debate. Trump is challenging Joe Biden to debate.
articles.title: Will Biden and Trump face one another in presidential debates? There's no commitment yet

articles.description: DUBAI, United Arab Emirates (AP) — A ship came under attack by two missiles in the key Bab el-Mandeb Strait on Monday, the latest assault believed to have been carried out by Yemen’s Houthi rebels.
articles.title: Yemen's Houthi rebels suspected of missile attack targeting a ship in the Bab el-Mandeb Strait

articles.description: QUETTA, Pakistan (AP) — Thousands of supporters of Pakistan's imprisoned former Prime Minister Imran Khan and members of other political parties blocked key highways and started a daylong strike in the volatile southwest Monday to protest alleged rigging of last week's elections.
articles.title: Khan supporters and other Pakistani parties block highways to protest election results

articles.author: DIANE JEANTET and FABIANO MAISONNAVE
articles.description: RIO DE JANEIRO (AP) — Carnival dancers took the biggest stage in Rio de Janeiro on Sunday night with their faces painted red in a traditional Indigenous manner, while percussionists had “Miners out” written across the skins of their drums.
articles.title: Rio's Carnival parade makes urgent plea to stop illegal mining in Indigenous lands

articles.author: CHRISTINA LARSON
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Nearly half of the world's migratory species are in decline, according to a new United Nations report released Monday. Many songbirds, sea turtles, whales, sharks and other migratory animals move to different environments with changing seasons and are imperiled by habitat loss, illegal hunting and fishing, pollution and climate change.
articles.title: Nearly half of the world’s migratory species are in decline, UN report says
